## 🏗️ Architecture Constraints

### File Organization
```
src/
├── components/        # React UI components
│   ├── layout/
│   ├── briefing/
│   ├── budget/
│   └── shared/
├── store/            # Zustand stores
├── schemas/          # TypeScript types/schemas
├── ai/               # AI agents and prompts
│   ├── agents/
│   ├── prompts/
│   ├── orchestrator/
│   └── providers/
├── lib/              # Utilities and helpers
├── telemetry/        # Telemetry instrumentation
└── App.tsx
```

### Naming Conventions
- **Components:** PascalCase (`BudgetSummary.tsx`)
- **Hooks:** camelCase with `use` prefix (`useBudgetStore.ts`)
- **Utilities:** camelCase (`formatCurrency.ts`)
- **Constants:** SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (`API_BASE_URL`)
- **Types/Interfaces:** PascalCase (`BudgetReport`, `CostSource`)

### Import Order
1. React and external libraries
2. Internal components
3. Stores and state
4. Utilities and helpers
5. Types and schemas
6. Styles

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
import { useState, useEffect } from "react";
